  "body": "<!--\r\nNeed help?\r\nRefer to our contributing guidelines for additional information about making a good issue:\r\nhttps://github.com/ethereum-optimism/.github/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md\r\n-->\r\n\r\n**Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.**\r\nWe have a bunch of hard-coded addresses all over the place. For example:\r\n* https://github.com/ethereum-optimism/optimism/blob/9fea7c94abb5b09a7a0c571370b79e20d7f365c0/packages/contracts/contracts/optimistic-ethereum/OVM/execution/OVM_ExecutionManager.sol#L554\r\n* https://github.com/ethereum-optimism/optimism/blob/9fea7c94abb5b09a7a0c571370b79e20d7f365c0/packages/contracts/contracts/optimistic-ethereum/OVM/execution/OVM_ExecutionManager.sol#L556\r\n* https://github.com/ethereum-optimism/optimism/blob/9fea7c94abb5b09a7a0c571370b79e20d7f365c0/packages/contracts/contracts/optimistic-ethereum/OVM/execution/OVM_ExecutionManager.sol#L832\r\n\r\netc etc\r\n\r\nAll addresses that start with 0x420.....XX are \"predeployed\" contracts that are injected into the state when the system is first deployed. [This file](https://github.com/ethereum-optimism/optimism/blob/develop/packages/contracts/src/predeploys.ts) is essentially the canonical list of these addresses at the moment. I'd like if we moved away from these hard-coded addresses and instead introduced a library that manages these constants.\r\n\r\n**Describe the solution you'd like**\r\n`Lib_PredeployAddresses` that looks something like:\r\n\r\n```\r\nlibrary Lib_PredeployAddresses {\r\n    address public constant ovmL2ToL1MessagePasser = 0x4200000000000000000000000000000000000000;\r\n    address public constant ovmL1MessageSender = 0x4200000000000000000000000000000000000001;\r\n    .... // etc etc\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nI think this library could probably go in a new folder `contracts/optimistic-ethereum/libraries/constants/Lib_PredeployAddresses.sol`\r\n\r\n**Describe alternatives you've considered**\r\nAlternatively, we could also just add a `Lib_Constants` that contains *all* of the constants that get used in various places. I'd be down for either approach.\r\n",
